[2] Israel - suspected cases, RFI
Date: 23 Jul 2013
Source: Yeshiva World News [edited]
http://www.theyeshivaworld.com/news/General+News/178764/Polio-Fears-in-Southern-Israel.html


According to a Channel 1 News report, 3 children from the Bedouin community of Tel Sheva and a 4th southern district child are feared to have contracted polio.

Health Ministry officials have been urging parents to have all children under 6 vaccinated after traces of polio were detected in Beersheva area sewers. In addition, traces of the virus were found recently in the Sharon Region sewage system. The system is connected to the Lev HaSharon, Kalansua, Jaljulia, Kfar Bara and Choreshim communities.

Health officials in the southern district in the past 2 weeks conducted tests on 1700 stool samples from adults and children from areas in which polio was detected in the sewage system. Additional testing is being conducted for those people whose stool samples tested positive. Health officials explain the children may be carrying the illness but remain asymptomatic.

Thousands of samples are being studied as well to determine how many children up the age of 8 carry the virus.

If these cases are confirmed, and if it is established that a large population carries the virus, the ministry is likely to give an additional vaccine to an estimated 150 000 children under the age of 8. A decision is expected within approximately 2 weeks.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This moderator has attempted to find more information on these supposedly suspected cases of polio in the Southern district to no avail. From the wording of the article, this moderator suspects that the "alleged" cases refer to asymptomatic carriers of the WPV; the article mentions 3 or possibly 4 such cases out of 1700 stool samples tested for WPV, whereas the newswire in the 1st section ([1]) mentions 7-10 positive samples out of 2300 stool specimens processed. The article is being presented here requesting clarification from knowledgeable sources in Israel. - Mod.MPP]

