[Since the last polio update, with information as of 10 Jul 2013, there have been 38 new cases reported, raising the global total of polio cases from 132 to 170. 32 of these cases have occurred in the ongoing outbreak in Somalia and Kenya, raising the total number of outbreak associated cases to 105 from 73. In Somalia, during this 3-week period (from 10-31 Jul 2013), there have been 30 newly identified cases, raising the total number of cases in Somalia to 95.

A disappointing observation is that the year-to-date total of confirmed cases of WPV associated polio for 2013 is now 170, whereas the year-to-date total for this same period in 2012 was 103.

For the map showing locations of all confirmed WPV cases in the world as of 30 Jul 2013, see http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring.aspx. - Mod.MPP]
